  "original_title": "\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dc3\u0dca \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dallas ready to be president",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the parliamentary tradition and the constitution, he is ready to compete for the executive presidency of the country, which is currently vacant, says Mr. Dallas Alahapperuma, a former minister and member of parliament.",
        "The resignation of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa was confirmed in today's meeting of the party leaders in the Parliament and it is a fact that you already know that the new President should be elected in a constitutional vote in the Parliament to complete his next term.",
        "The Sri Lankan people are experiencing a period of transition, experiencing many political, economic and social activities unprecedented in history.",
        "The political authorities have been able to break the public opposition that arose through an economic crisis. Because of that, the direction of people's expectations has changed.",
        "I strongly believe that the people of this country should not suffer any more hardship, hardship or frustration under such circumstances.",
        "From the small school child to the retired adult, it is evident that there is a constant desire and interest to find a sustainable solution to the crises.",
        "As a developed cultural society, all these should be solved within a democratic constitutional political framework.",
        "It is no secret that I have been engaged in active politics for three decades and have always stood by the people of this country.",
        "It is an indisputable fact that the current political confusions should be resolved quickly through the Parliament. In order to solve the current economic crisis, an economic plan agreed upon by all of us must be prepared and implemented immediately. For that, the support of brother religious leaders led by the Maha Sangharatna, young political activists and professionals should be sought inside and outside the parliament.",
        "It can be assured that I am a friendly and reliable politician who can get the support and agreement of all of them.",
        "I respectfully inform the people of this country that I am ready to compete for the currently vacant executive presidency of the country in accordance with the parliamentary tradition and the constitution, for the sake of the overall public good and to establish a civilized political culture in this country, without political color glasses and for that without traditional divisions. I also expect the unwavering support of the philanthropic parliamentarians who have the sincere aim of building a peaceful and developed Sri Lanka.",
        "I have declared with responsibility that I will dedicate myself single-mindedly to the duties and sacrifices that can and should be done to take this motherland towards economic prosperity while preserving the rule of law and harmony between nations."
      ],
